  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And so when my sister left the country, my parents brought her to the train station [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And she wanted to kiss my parents goodbye, but the SS guards pulled her away and didn't let her kiss my parents goodbye.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And she never saw them again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] And then soon after, my father died.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he had been in the concentration camp in Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And that happened after the so-called Kristallnacht that all Jewish establishments were destroyed, and all Jewish males-- all Jewish males that they could get hold of-- were interned in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And when my father came after, it was-- he wasn't walking then.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "He had a stroke.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] somehow he made his way home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But he was-- he was not-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it's like psychologically, he was also not normal anymore.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "He started screaming sometimes in the middle of the day, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And, yeah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My sister was still there at that time, when they-- our store was ransacked.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And they came-- that's what I know from my sister, because I wasn't there anymore.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I was in Palestine at the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And my sister told me all of this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And they came at night, in the evening, and broke our big shop windows, you know, and threw all the merchandise out into the street.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And then around four o'clock in the morning, they came up and told my sister and my father [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to pick up all the shards, the glass, with their bare hands, and threw things at them, shoes and boots at them.",
      "word_count": 44
    }
  ],
